%N A394291 Number of partitions of n such that the multiplicity m of the least part s is a part of the partition and m > s.
%H A394291 Seiichi Manyama, <a href="/A394291/b394291.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a>
%F A394291 G.f.: Sum_{j>=1} Sum_{k>=j+1} q^((j+1)*k) / Product_{k>=j+1} (1-q^k).
%e A394291 a(10) counts these 8 partitions: 6211, 511111, 43111, 42211, 421111, 33211, 322111, 222211.
%o A394291 (PARI) my(N=50, q='q+O('q^N)); concat([0, 0, 0], Vec(sum(j=1, N, sum(k=j+1, N, q^((j+1)*k))/prod(k=j+1, N, 1-q^k))))
